prompt:
You are a friendly and encouraging faculty evaluator. Your goal is to provide a "faculty-like" evaluation for a beginner student: 
- **Be forgiving**: Students are beginners. Do not penalize for minor syntax errors, spelling, or small visual differences.
- **Reward effort**: If a student has made a genuine attempt with many lines of code, they should easily pass (Score 80+).
- **Correct but helpful**: Point out major logical flaws, but do it constructively. 
- **Not over-strict**: If the page "looks and works" mostly as expected, give high marks.

Focus Area: UI/UX & Styling (HTML/CSS)
Course Context: General programming evaluation.

**GRADING PRINCIPLES:**
1. Genuine effort/Mostly complete: Score **85-100**.
2. Partially complete/Good progress: Score **80-84**.
3. Only fail (Score < 80) if clearly blank or completely unrelated boilerplate.
4. Value understanding and effort over pixel-perfection.

---

CHALLENGE
Title: Level 1 - Question 29
Description: Create an HTML-only page for a museum exhibit with detailed descriptions, images, and event schedules.
Instructions: Requirements:
1. Organize exhibit details using <section> for different themes (e.g., Ancient Artifacts, Modern Art).
2. Display exhibit images with <figure> and <img>, with alt text and captions.
3. Include a video or virtual tour of the museum.
4. Add a <footer> with museum hours and contact information.
5. Use <meta> tags for responsive design.

---

STUDENT CODE
HTML: <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Local museum exhibit showcasing ancient artifacts and modern art">
    <title>Local Museum Exhibit</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 12px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        header, footer {
            background: #5a3e2b;
            color: white;
            padding: 16px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        section {
            margin: 25px 0;
        }

        figure {
            margin: 0;
            text-align: center;
        }

        img {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 300px;
        }

        figcaption {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: #444;
            margin-top: 6px;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        video {
            width: 100%;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    <h1>Local Heritage Museum</h1>
    <p>Explore the wonders of history and art!</p>
</header>

<section>
    <h2>Ancient Artifacts</h2>
    <p>Discover rare and priceless relics from ancient civilizations.</p>

    <figure>
        <img src="ancient-artifact.jpg" alt="Ancient pottery artifact">
        <figcaption>Clay Pottery - 2000 BCE</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure>
        <img src="ancient-weapon.jpg" alt="Ancient bronze weapon">
        <figcaption>Bronze Dagger - 1500 BCE</figcaption>
    </figure>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Modern Art</h2>
    <p>A vibrant journey through contemporary creativity and expression.</p>

    <figure>
        <img src="modern-painting.jpg" alt="Abstract modern painting">
        <figcaption>"Colors of Freedom" - 2021</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <figure>
        <img src="sculpture-modern.jpg" alt="Modern sculpture artwork">
        <figcaption>Steel Horizons - 2019</figcaption>
    </figure>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Exhibit Schedule</h2>
    <p>Daily Tours:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>10:00 AM – Ancient Wander</li>
        <li>12:00 PM – The Rise of Art</li>
        <li>03:00 PM – Sculpture Stories</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Virtual Tour</h2>
    <video controls>
        <source src="museum-tour.mp4" type="video/mp4">
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>
</section>

<footer>
    <h3>Visit Us</h3>
    <p>Opening Hours: 9:00 AM – 7:00 PM (Mon–Sun)</p>
    <p>Email: <a href="mailto:info@localmuseum.com">info@localmuseum.com</a></p>
    <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+18001234567">+1 800 123 4567</a></p>
    <p>&copy; 2025 Local Heritage Museum</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>

CSS: No CSS provided
JavaScript: No JS provided

---

